In Acumatica ERP, service order types are used to define the general settings for service orders and appointments associated with the particular type.{br}
In this topic, you will read about creating service order types and specifying their main settings during creation.{br}{TOC} ==Creating a Service Order Type== You create a service order type on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202300|FS202300]) form. For each service order type, you specify the following:[anchor|#ul_jsy_jsd_ky] *The numbering sequence to be used for the reference numbers of orders of the type *The behavior of the type, which determines the availability of certain form elements for service orders and appointments of the type *General settings *Default settings of service orders and appointments of the type *Billing settings (that is, the settings related to billing customers for service orders of the type) *Settings that affect integration between appointments of the type and forms in the system that track the time that staff members spend on attending appointments or performing services {br}
These types of settings are described in the sections of this topic. You can specify additional settings for the service order type, such as problem codes, attributes, mailing settings, and time preferences for the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form for appointments of this type. Also, you can configure quick processing for the service order type so that users can process the service orders and appointments of this type with just one click. For details, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Configuration_of_QP|Configuration of Quick Processing]. ==Selecting a Behavior== Depending on the behavior you select for the service order type, the system makes particular boxes and tabs available or unavailable on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types], [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_01_00|Service Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300100|FS300100]), and [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) forms. You can select one of the following behaviors for the service order type:[anchor|#_083da7eb-657a-4155-a041-16a5293c24f4] *''Regular'': You select this behavior if service orders of the type will include the usual services, such as repair, maintenance, installation, and training. For this behavior, you can set up all the settings except the route-related settings. *''Route'': You select this behavior if service orders of the type include details of the route between locations where services are performed. For the service order types with this behavior, the route can be specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form. For details on routes, see the [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__MNG_Routes|Managing Routes] chapter in the Route Management guide. *''Internal'': You select this behavior for a type that includes service orders of your own company, and appointments take place inside the company. Because there is no customer involved with the service orders of the type with this behavior, the posting, customer, and route settings are unavailable for the service orders of this type. *''Quote'': You select this behavior a type designed for quotes (which can be converted into service orders if the customer agrees to the quote). For types with this behavior, posting settings are unavailable on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] form.
==Specifying the Default Settings== For appointments of the service order type, you can define the default source of the address for the appointment, which is specified in documents related to the appointment. In the '''Default Settings''' section on the '''Preferences''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] form, in the '''Take Address and Contact Information From''' box, you select one of the following options:[anchor|#_a96e68df-5487-4c59-ad51-d24c58015b2a] *''Business Account'': Select this button when the appointments of the type generally take place at the main address—that is, the address that is specified in the '''Main Address''' section on the '''General Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\AR_30_30_00|Customers] ([~/?ScreenId=AR303000|AR303000]) form. *''Contact'': Select this button when the appointments of the type generally take place at the address of the customer&rsquo;s contact person—that is, at the address that is specified in the '''Address''' section on the '''General Info''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form. *''Branch Location'': Select this button when the appointments of this type generally take place at the address of your branch location—that is, at the address that is specified for the branch location in the '''Main Address''' section of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_25_00|Branch Locations] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202500|FS202500]) form. {br}
Also, in the '''Default Settings''' section, you can specify a salesperson that will be assigned by default to the service orders and appointments of the type and whether the commission is paid to this salesperson or not. ==Specifying the Invoice Generation Settings== The invoice generation settings define the type of the documents for customer billing that are generated for appointments or service orders of the service order type, and the general settings for these documents. You specify these settings in the '''Invoice Generation Settings''' section of the '''Preferences''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] form. You select the billing document as follows:[anchor|#_85611c6e-0ddd-4201-8948-4c12cfe2f075] *If you need to generate a billing document for services (of the service order type) only, you select the '''Accounts Receivable''' option button under '''Generate Invoices In'''. With this option selected, the system generates an accounts receivable invoice when a user invokes document generation for a service order or appointment. The invoice can then be processed and the payment collected. *:If the '''Create a Bill Document in AP for Negative Balances''' check box (which is available if you select this option button) is selected, for the service order or appointment with a negative balance, the system instead creates an accounts payable bill. *If you need to generate a billing document for both services (of the service order type) and inventory items (which may involve shipping) that were sold to customers along with the services, you select the '''Sales Orders''' option button under '''Generate Invoices In'''. With this option selected, the system initially generates a sales order when a user invokes invoice generation. Optionally, you can create shipments and add freight costs for the sales order. You then generate the invoice. If you have configured quick processing for the service order type, the invoice can be generated automatically along with the sales order. For details about quick processing, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Quick_Processing_Workflow|Quick Processing of Service Orders and Appointments]. *:((({S:Hint}Integration with field services has to be enabled for the sales order type so that you can generate sales orders from forms related to field services. That is, the '''Enable Field Services Integration''' check box has to be selected for the necessary order type on the '''General Settings '''tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SO_20_10_00|Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=SO201000|SO201000]) form. ))) *If you need to generate a billing document for both services (of the service order type) and inventory items (which do not involve shipping) that were sold to customers along with the services, you select the '''SO Invoice''' option button under '''Generate Invoices In'''. With this option selected, the system initially generates an SO invoice when a user invokes invoice generation. If you have configured quick processing for the service order type, the invoice can be processed automatically in the system. *If you do not need to generate invoices for the customer for services of the service order type, you select the '''None''' option button under '''Generate Invoices In''' group. {br}
When you have selected the option button, you specify the default settings for it (also in the '''Invoice Generation Settings''' section) to be used in the invoice documents. ==Setting Up the Time & Expenses Integration== In the '''Time & Expenses Integration''' section of the '''Preferences''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202300|FS202300]) form, you can set up integration with the forms on which time activities are tracked for the service order type if the '''Enable Time & Expenses Integration''' check box is selected in the '''Integrating with Time & Expenses''' section on the '''General Settings''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_10_01_00|Service Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=FS100100|FS100100]) form. You need to select the '''Require Time Approval to Close Appointments''' check box if you want to set up approval (by an employee with this responsibility) of the time spent performing services of the type. {br}
In this section, you can also select the '''Automatically Create Time Activities from Appointments''' check box to set up the automatic creation of time activities; you have to also specify the default earning type for the time activities. For details, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Integration_TimeExpenses|Integration with Time & Expenses]. [anchor|#_27957a1a-ff98-4359-88b0-ff600f3387d0] ==Specifying Attributes for Service Orders, Appointments, and Service Contract Schedules== An attribute is a site-defined property (for instance, industry or problem type) that gives users the ability to specify information for objects in the system beyond the preconfigured settings on the data entry forms. In the settings of a service order type, you can specify attributes for the classification of service orders, appointments, and service schedules. The applicable set of attributes is specified for a particular service order type on the '''Attributes''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202300|FS202300]) form. {br}
On this tab, you can select attributes only if they have already been defined in the system. If you need an attribute that has not been defined in the system, you can use the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_20_50_00|Attributes] ([~/?ScreenId=CS205000|CS205000]) form to create the attribute. Then you will be able to select the new attribute for any service order type.{br}
The attributes you specify on this tab will be listed for service orders and appointments of this service order type on the '''Attributes''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_01_00|Service Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300100|FS300100]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) forms, respectively. The system also copies the active attributes on this tab to the service schedules of this service order type on the '''Attributes''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_51_00|Service Contract Schedules] ([~/?ScreenId=FS305100|FS305100]) and [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_56_00|Route Service Contract Schedules] ([~/?ScreenId=FS305600|FS305600]) forms. {br}
On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] form, you can specify whether each attribute of the service order type is required. When creating a service order, appointment, or service schedule of the service order type, the user must specify values for all the required attributes. Also, you can specify default values for any attributes of the type; users can overwrite these values for a particular service order, appointment, or service schedule of the type.{br}
You can deactivate an obsolete attribute for service orders and appointments of a particular type by clearing the '''Active''' check box on this tab. If you do, the deactivated attribute will no longer be displayed for the service orders, appointments, and service schedules of the type, but all attribute values that have already been specified for existing service orders, appointments, and service schedules will still be stored in the database. If you re-activate the attribute, its values (where specified) will become visible in the system again. {br}
However, if it is not necessary to preserve the data related to an obsolete attribute, you can deactivate the attribute and then delete it by using the '''Delete Row''' button on the table toolbar. In this case, the attribute will be permanently deleted from the service order type, and all attribute values will be deleted from the database. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_Administration\CS__con_Attributes_and_User_Defined_Fields|Managing Attributes and User-Defined Fields] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Appointments|Appointment Creation] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Billing_Cycle|Billing Cycle Settings] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Service_Creation|Service Order Entry] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Integration_TimeExpenses|Integration with Time & Expenses] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Quick_Processing_Workflow|Quick Processing of Service Orders and Appointments] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_60_00|Billing Cycles] ([~/?ScreenId=FS206000|FS206000]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202300|FS202300]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_01_00|Service Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300100|FS300100])

In Acumatica ERP, you can simplify the standard multi-step processing of service orders and appointments, and configure quick processing for a particular service order type so that users can process the service orders and appointments of this type with just one click.{br}
In this topic, you will read about the configuration of quick processing of service orders and appointments. ==Configuring Quick Processing for a Service Order Type== For quick processing to be used for service orders and appointments of a particular service order type, you must allow quick processing for this service order type and specify the actions to be performed during quick processing. To allow quick processing for the service order type, you select the '''Allow Quick Process''' check box on the '''Preferences''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202300|FS202300]) form. This causes the '''Quick Process Settings''' tab to appear on the form. On this tab, you configure the set of processing actions to be used by default for service orders and appointments of this type. {br}
For each particular service order or appointment of the type being processed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_01_00|Service Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300100|FS300100]) or [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form, the list of actions to be performed can be changed. For instructions on configuring an order type for quick processing, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__HOW_To_Configur_Quick_Processing|To Configure Quick Processing for a Service Order Type].((({S:Hint}Quick processing can be configured for service order types that are defined to initially generate sales orders from service orders or appointments (that is, the '''Sales Orders''' option button is selected in the '''Generate Invoices From''' section of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] form). ))) Also, the service order lines that are marked for purchasing—that is, those with the '''Mark for PO''' check box selected on the '''Services''' or '''Inventory Item''' tab or both of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_01_00|Service Orders] form—are excluded from quick processing because the creation of a purchase order is not included in the quick processing configuration flow. ==Related Articles== *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_SO_Integration|Integration of Sales Orders and Service Orders] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Service_Order_Types|Service Order Types] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__con_Quick_Process_Workflow|Quick Processing of Sales Orders] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Quick_Processing_Workflow|Quick Processing of Service Orders and Appointments] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__HOW_To_Configur_Quick_Processing|To Configure Quick Processing for a Service Order Type] *[HelpRoot_OrderMgmt\SO__How_Configure_Quick_Processing|To Configure Quick Processing for an Order Type] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__HOW_To_Quickly_Process_Service_Order|To Quickly Process a Service Order] *[HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__HOW_To_Quickly_Process_Appointment|To Quickly Process an Appointment] *[HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202300|FS202300]) *[HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_01_00|Service Orders] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300100|FS300100])

