The time that staff members spend on attending appointments or performing services can be reported automatically on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_70_00|Employee Time Activities] ([~/?ScreenId=EP307000|EP307000]) form. If a staff member works during the entire appointment or a part of the appointment, the appointment time is registered in the time activity. If a staff member performs only particular services of the appointment, the service time is registered in the time activity of the staff member.{br}
In this topic, you will read about configuring the system to make this integration possible, registering appointment staff time, registering service staff time, and updating appointments and time activities.{br}{TOC} ==Configuration of Tracking of Time Activities for Staff Members== To make the system automatically create the applicable time activities for staff members on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_70_00|Employee Time Activities] ([~/?ScreenId=EP307000|EP307000]) form when appointments are completed on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form, you should configure the system as follows:[anchor|#_9e88d4d1-ba0b-4d10-b55e-d156922577bd] #You ensure that the ''Time Reporting on Activity'' feature is enabled on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\CS_10_00_00|Enable/Disable Features] ([~/?ScreenId=CS100000|CS100000]) form. #You ensure that the required settings are specified on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_10_10_00|Time and Expenses Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=EP101000|EP101000]) form. #You select the '''Enable Time & Expenses Integration''' check box on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_10_01_00|Service Management Preferences] ([~/?ScreenId=FS100100|FS100100]) form. #For each service order type for which time activities should be created, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_20_23_00|Service Order Types] ([~/?ScreenId=FS202300|FS202300]) form, you make sure that the '''Automatically Create Time Activities from Appointments''' check box is selected, and you select the default earning type to be used for the hours spent performing the appointments in the '''Default Earning Type''' box. #:((({S:Hint}You can also define an earning type for each service in the '''Service Management''' section of the '''Price/Cost Information''' tab on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_40_08_00|Services] ([~/?ScreenId=FS400800|FS400800]) form. The earning type for the service would have a higher priority than the default earning type for the service order type. ))) #For each staff member to perform services, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\SM_20_10_10|Users] ([~/?ScreenId=SM201010|SM201010]) form, you verify that the '''Linked Entity''' box is filled with the user login name.
==Registration of Staff Time for the Entire Appointment == For all staff members that work during the entire duration of an appointment, to track the staff time, you assign these staff members to the appointment but do not associate them with any service. That is, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form, you assign the necessary staff members to the appointment on the '''Staff''' tab and leave the '''Service ID''' column empty for these staff members.{br}
When the staff member performs the appointment, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form (the '''Actual Date and Time''' section of the '''Summary''' tab), he or she enters the time when the appointment has started in the '''Actual Start Time''' box and the time when the appointment has ended in the '''Actual End Time''' box. For details on processing appointments, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Appointment_Processing|Appointment Processing Workflow].{br}
When the appointment is completed (that is, when a staff member invokes the '''Complete Appointment''' action on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form), the system copies the appointment times from the '''Actual Start Time''' and '''Actual End Time''' boxes of the '''Summary''' tab to the '''Actual Start Time''' and '''Actual End Time''' boxes of the '''Staff''' tab. {br}
The system also automatically creates a time activity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_70_00|Employee Time Activities] ([~/?ScreenId=EP307000|EP307000]) form for each staff member assigned to the appointment. The '''Start Time''' of the time activity is the '''Actual Start Time''' of the staff member on the '''Staff''' tab on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form. The '''Time Spent''' of the time activity is the difference between the '''Actual End Time''' and '''Actual Start Time''' of the staff member on the '''Staff''' tab. ==Registration of Staff Time for a Part of the Appointment == If a staff member is working on the appointment only during a specific part of the appointment but not during the entire appointment, to correctly track the staff time, you assign the applicable staff members to the appointment but do not associate them with any service. That is, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form, you assign the necessary staff members to the appointment on the '''Staff''' tab and leave the '''Service ID''' column empty for these staff members.{br}
When the staff member performs the appointment, on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form (the '''Actual Date and Time''' section of the '''Summary''' tab), he or she enters the time when the appointment has started in the '''Actual Start Time''' box, the time when the appointment has ended in the '''Actual End Time''' box, and the actual time he or she has worked in the '''Actual Duration''' box on the '''Staff''' tab. For details on processing appointments, see [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Appointment_Processing|Appointment Processing Workflow].{br}
When the appointment is completed (that is, when a staff member invokes the '''Complete Appointment''' action on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form), the system copies the appointment times from the '''Actual Start Time''' box of the '''Summary''' tab to the '''Actual Start Time''' box of the '''Staff''' tab and calculates '''Actual End Time''' as a sum of the actual start time and duration. {br}
The system also automatically creates a time activity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_70_00|Employee Time Activities] ([~/?ScreenId=EP307000|EP307000]) form for each staff member assigned to the appointment. The '''Start Time''' of the time activity is the '''Actual Start Time''' of the '''Staff''' tab on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form. The '''Time Spent''' of the time activity is the difference between the '''Actual End Time''' and '''Actual Start Time''' of the staff member on '''Staff''' tab. ==Registration of Service Staff Time== If a staff member is working on the appointment during only particular services (or one service) but not during all services, to correctly track the staff time, you associate the staff member with the services he or she is performing on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form. You can assign a staff member to a service line in the following ways: [anchor|#_7323650c-1952-42b7-8cd3-deeba92e5aa9] *If the service is performed by only one staff member, by selecting this staff member in the '''Staff Member ID''' column of the service line on the '''Services''' tab *By clicking the service line and then clicking the '''Staff Selector''' button on the '''Services''' tab and selecting the staff member in the '''Staff Selector''' dialog box *By clicking the '''Staff Selector''' button on the '''Staff''' tab, selecting a service line in the '''Service Line Ref.''' box, and selecting the staff member in the '''Staff Selector''' dialog box *By selecting the service line reference number in the '''Service Line Ref.''' column on the '''Staff''' tab for the staff member
During the appointment, on the '''Services''' tab of the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form, staff members should enter the actual start and end times of particular services in the '''Actual Start Time''' and '''Actual End Time''' columns, respectively.{br}
When the appointment is completed (that is, when a staff member invokes the '''Complete Appointment''' action on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form), the system automatically creates the time activity on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_70_00|Employee Time Activities] ([~/?ScreenId=EP307000|EP307000]) form for each staff member assigned to the appointment. If the staff member is assigned to one service, the '''Start Time''' of the time activity is the '''Actual Start Time''' of the service performed by the staff member on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] form; the '''Time Spent''' of the time activity is the '''Actual Duration''' of the service. If the staff member is assigned to multiple services, the '''Time Spent''' of the time activity is the sum of the actual durations of the services. ==Actions that Invoke Automatic Updates of Time Activities== On the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form, you can correct appointments, which causes the existing employee time activity records to be updated accordingly on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\EP_30_70_00|Employee Time Activities] ([~/?ScreenId=EP307000|EP307000]) form. The system automatically makes corresponding updates to time activities under the following circumstances:[anchor|#_626bc4cf-d675-496e-ba65-2f6740cc858f] *When you change the staff member who performed a service or the entire appointment on the '''Staff''' tab. In this case, the system deletes the time activity of the previous staff member and adds a new time activity for the newly selected staff member. *If time was recorded for the entire appointment or a part of the appointment, when you change the start and end times in the '''Actual Start Time''' and '''Actual End Time''' columns of the '''Staff''' tab of the related staff member. Under these circumstances, in the time activity, the system updates the start time and the time spent. *If time was recorded for any service, when you change the start and end times in the '''Actual Start Time''' and '''Actual End Time''' columns of the '''Services''' or '''Staff''' tab. In this case, in the time activity, the system updates the actual duration of the service and the time spent by the staff member. *When you clear the '''Track Time''' check box on the '''Staff''' tab. This action causes the system to delete the time activity record. If you select this check box again, the system will add the time activity record. *When you reopen the appointment. In this case, the system deletes all time activity records. The records will again be created when the appointment is completed.
