To update the Inventory module with the items picked up or delivered while the route was executed, you have to specify them on the [HelpRoot_FormReference\FS_30_02_00|Appointments] ([~/?ScreenId=FS300200|FS300200]) form. ==Before You Proceed== To be able to add inventory items to the appointment, the inventory items have to be configured, as described in [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__CON_Configuraton_Inventory|Configuration of the System for Inventory Updates]. ==To Specify Picked Up or Delivered Items in an Appointment== #On the '''Services''' tab, click '''Service Management'''. In the left pane, navigate to '''Work Area''' > '''Enter''' > '''Appointments'''. #In the '''Service Order Type''' box, select the service order type of the ''Route'' behavior related to the appointment in which you want to specify the items. #In the '''Service Order Nbr.''' box, select the service order for which the appointment was created. #In the '''Appointment Nbr.''' box, select the appointment in which you want to specify the items. #If services have not yet been added to the appointment, add them on the '''Services''' tab, as described in [HelpRoot_FieldServices\FS__HOW_To_Add_Service_to_SO|To Add Services to a Service Order or Appointment]. #To add items that will be delivered to the customer at this appointment, on the '''Pickup/Delivery Items''' tab, do the following for each item you want to add: ##In the '''Line Ref.''' column, select the reference number of the service line (that is assigned to the service on the '''Services''' tab) to which the item is related. ##In the '''Pickup/Delivery Item ID''' column, select the delivered item by its identifier. ##In the '''Warehouse''' column, select the warehouse from which the item is taken in the appropriate quantity. ##In the '''Quantity''' column, specify the quantity of the item. ##Check the '''Unit Price''' column, and change the price of the item if necessary. #To add items that will be picked up from the customer on this appoin